<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25784</anchor> <rss>anon.198.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.198</addr>  <route>anon.198.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>This follows from two existing lemmas:</p>

  <ol><li><link href="jms-0025.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0025" title="Lifted dcpos are positively generated">Lifted dcpos (free algebras) are positively generated</link>.</li>
    <li><link href="jms-002A.xml" type="local" addr="jms-002A" title="Positively generated pointed dcpos are free">Positively generated pointed dcpos are free</link>.</li></ol>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25785</anchor> <rss>jms-002B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>jms-002B</addr>  <route>jms-002B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tomdejong.xml" type="local" tomdejong="addr">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martinescardo.xml" type="local" martinescardo="addr">Martín Hötzel Escardó</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Liftedness = positive generation</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-001S.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001S" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</link> dcpo <tex>A</tex> is lifted if and only if it is <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25786</anchor> <rss>jms-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-0025</addr>  <route>jms-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifted dcpos are positively generated</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a dcpo; then the lift <tex>\mathsf { L } {A}</tex> is <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25787</anchor> <rss>anon.254.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.254</addr>  <route>anon.254.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Let <tex>u= { \mathopen {} \left ( \phi ,a \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> be an element of <tex>\mathsf { L } {A}</tex>. Note that <tex>u</tex> is equal to <tex>\bigsqcup _{p: \phi }u</tex>; as <link href="jms-001N.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001N" title="Positivity = definedness in a lifted dcpo">definedness coincides with positivity</link> in lifted dcpos, we have <tex>\phi  =  \mathsf { pos } \, u</tex>, and so we are done.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25788</anchor> <rss>jms-002A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-002A</addr>  <route>jms-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tomdejong.xml" type="local" tomdejong="addr">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martinescardo.xml" type="local" martinescardo="addr">Martín Hötzel Escardó</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Positively generated pointed dcpos are free</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link> <link href="jms-001S.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001S" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</link> dcpo; then <tex>A</tex> is canonically <em>free</em> on its <link href="jms-001P.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001P" title="The subdcpo spanned by positive elements">subdcpo of positive elements</link> <tex>A^+</tex>. More specifically, the embedding-projection pair <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf { L } { \iota ^+}; \alpha _A \right ) \mathclose {}} \dashv { A } \xrightarrow {{ \mathsf { purify } _A }}{ \mathsf { L } {A^+} }</tex> <link href="jms-0020.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0020" title="Pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free">given by</link> the <link href="jms-0021.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0021" title="The “purification” map">purification map</link> is an isomorphism of dcpos.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25789</anchor> <rss>anon.267.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.267</addr>  <route>anon.267.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>First, we recall that the embedding-projection pair <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf { L } { \iota ^+}; \alpha _A \right ) \mathclose {}} \dashv \mathsf { purify } _A</tex> <link href="jms-0020.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0020" title="Pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free">exists</link> because <tex>A</tex> has an <link href="jms-0022.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0022" title="Open positivity predicate">open positivity predicate</link> by <link href="jms-0027.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0027" title="Positively generated dcpos have open positivity predicates">virtue of</link> its <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positive generation</link>. Therefore, the statement of this lemma is well-formed.</p>

  <p>Because <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf { L } { \iota ^+}; \alpha _A \right ) \mathclose {}} \dashv \mathsf { purify } _A</tex> is an embedding-projection pair, it remains only to check that <tex>\mathsf { purify } _A; \mathsf { L } { \iota ^+}; \alpha _A</tex> is an <em>inflation</em>, i.e. for all <tex>a:A</tex> we must have <tex>a  \sqsubseteq   \alpha _A { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf { L } { \iota ^+} { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf { purify } _Aa \right ) \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex>. As the latter is equal to <tex>\bigsqcup _{p: \mathsf { pos } \, a}a</tex>, the inflation condition follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>